py array as input_grid and the minimum and maximum x and y coordinates of all the blue points in the grid.\n    It finds all the blue points within the area [minx:maxx,miny:maxy] (not including the edge) and returns their same column or row.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array of shape (n, m) containing integers from 0 to 9 representing different colors.\n    minx: An integer representing the minimum x coordinate of all the blue points in the grid.\n    miny: An integer representing the minimum y coordinate of all the blue points in the grid.\n    maxx: An integer representing the maximum x coordinate of all the blue points in the grid.\n    maxy: An integer representing the maximum y coordinate of all the blue points in the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of integers representing the same column or row of all the blue points within the area [minx:maxx,miny:maxy] (not including the edge).\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_points = np.where(input_grid[minx + 1:maxx, miny + 1:maxy] == blue)\n    if len(blue_points[0]) == 0:\n        return []\n    if blue_points[0][0] == 0:\n        return blue_points[1].tolist()\n    if blue_points[1][0] == 0:\n        return blue_points[0].tolist()\n    return []", "holes": {"find_blue_points": "find all blue points in the grid, return its min x,min y, max x, max y coordinate", "color_edge_black_points_red": "Color the black points in the edge of area [minx:maxx,miny:maxy] red", "color_line_black_points_red": "test if row line_numcolor or column line_num have more than one blue points.All black points that in the line and within the area [minx:maxx,miny:maxy] red", "find_blue_points_within_area": "find all blue points within the area [minx:maxx,miny:maxy] (not including the edge), return their same column or row"}}
